# CS11b: Force LF line endings for all repo text files.
#
# The harness self-host swap (CS11) renders templates → root files via
# `applyTemplating()`, which produces LF output. On Windows, git's
# `core.autocrlf=true` converts LF → CRLF on checkout, causing
# `harness sync --mode=check` to detect false drift.
#
# This `.gitattributes` forces LF for all text files in the repo, so the
# working-tree state matches what the templating engine produces, and the
# CI drift gate stays accurate cross-platform.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary types — left as-is.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tar binary
